    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF ARCHIVED RECORDING)</p>
    <p>DAVID FARMER: We just want to make sure that it's - it just stays relevant.</p>
    <p>SHAPIRO: For one man, the irony of all this was just too delicious.</p>
    <p>ROBERT MULLER-MOORE: Really, could you script it any funnier than this?</p>
    <p>SHAPIRO: Meet Robert Muller-Moore.</p>
    <p>MULLER-MOORE: But everybody calls me Bo, the eat-more-kale guy.</p>
    <p>SHAPIRO: Eat more kale is the slogan he prints on a popular series of T-shirts at his studio in Vermont. Back in 2011, he got into a long legal fight with Chick-fil-A over those shirts. The company said it was too close to their tagline, eat more chicken. After three years, Muller-Moore won the fight. He got the trademark to eat more kale, and Chick-fil-A was out of his life.</p>
